Package MazeObjects

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bottom
    The Bottom MazeObject is invisible and exists only to prevent the array in the maze file from having nothing in some of the places in the array of stack descriptions.
    Box
    the class box is used to put the maze object box in the maze. the box used to create walls.
    CustomMazeObject
    the class customMazeObject is used to place custom objects in the maze that are imported from a .obj file Like all MazeObjects, it implements a translate method that returns a copy of the maze object moved to a different location, and a very weak equals method that acts as a somewhat more specific version of the instanceof operator.
    Empty
    The empty MAzeObejcts adds a empty block of a given size to the maze.
    Face
    the class face is used to give the all the objects its faces, these fases are used to detect collision.
    FinishTile
    the finishTile is the finish of the game when the player is on this tile the game is finished.
    Floor
    The Floor maze object defines a floor tile in the maze.
    MazeObject
    Class that contains the a number of points, represented by vectors, and faces, to create three dimensional objects that are in the maze.
    Pit
    The pit objects is the abyss like MazeObject placed under the lowest visible block of the Maze.
    Ramp
    The ramp object is a MazeObject that resembles a slope.
    SkyBox
    The SkyBox is the mazeObject on which the surounding sky texture is projected.
    StartTile
    This Mazeobject defines the start position of the player, and its rotation defines the orientation of the player ate the start of the level.
